2
00:00:00,010 --> 00:00:06,500
Chocolat Town
Totto Land

3
00:00:13,880 --> 00:00:17,080
Leave or life?

4
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:19,200
Life.

5
00:00:22,550 --> 00:00:25,740
Leave or life?

6
00:00:25,740 --> 00:00:26,860
Life.

7
00:00:44,470 --> 00:00:48,560
Leave or life?

8
00:02:35,790 --> 00:02:38,220
What's going on?!

9
00:02:35,830 --> 00:02:38,170
Lola's Vivre Card

10
00:02:38,220 --> 00:02:42,450
They've multiplied 
and are barking like animals!

11
00:02:38,250 --> 00:02:42,220
Seducing Woods

12
00:02:42,450 --> 00:02:44,510
What happened to you guys?!

13
00:02:46,010 --> 00:02:48,440
Aren't any of you real?!

14
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:50,020
Hey, Sanji!

15
00:02:52,260 --> 00:02:54,600
Pudding! Chopper!

16
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:55,940
Carrot!

17
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:58,530
Nami!

18
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:00,990
Untie me!

19
00:03:03,790 --> 00:03:06,510
She's talking like a human!

20
00:03:06,510 --> 00:03:08,160
I'm the real one!

21
00:03:10,860 --> 00:03:14,610
Listen up! I was looking for you!

22
00:03:14,610 --> 00:03:16,780
Why did you just grab me like that?!

23
00:03:16,780 --> 00:03:20,890
I... I'm really... really sorry...

24
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:25,470
But this is pretty crazy.
What's going on?

25
00:03:29,020 --> 00:03:31,840
This one certainly looks like me.

26
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:36,480
This would be easy if the real ones 
were all among them.

27
00:03:37,660 --> 00:03:39,610
Well, you guys were the ones who multiplied!

28
00:03:39,610 --> 00:03:42,640
We can't multiply!
I mean, we did, but...

29
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:48,490
Hey, you!

30
00:03:48,490 --> 00:03:50,120
What?!

31
00:03:49,410 --> 00:03:50,120
Huh?!

32
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:52,410
You know what happened, don't you?

33
00:03:52,410 --> 00:03:56,480
You were here the whole time, 
even when we were attacked by that woman!

34
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:58,020
I didn't see anything!

35
00:03:58,020 --> 00:04:00,280
Hey, what happened?

36
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:03,780
I was attacked by you, Luffy!

37
00:04:03,780 --> 00:04:04,890
By me?!

38
00:04:04,890 --> 00:04:10,400
Technically, it wasn't you. 
But it was a fake that we tried to escape with!

39
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,190
Huh? What do you mean?

40
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,620
Uh...

41
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:20,740
Then, that "Luffy" suddenly turned into
a giant woman... and attacked us...

42
00:04:26,940 --> 00:04:28,680
Let go of me!

43
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:29,930
Who are you?!

44
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:33,940
I'm Brûlée!

45
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:35,570
Brûlée?

46
00:04:35,570 --> 00:04:41,300
A cute rabbit and a pretty girl...
How nice...

47
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:44,960
When I see those beautiful faces,

48
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:48,410
it makes me want to scratch them up!

49
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:51,240
Nami!

50
00:04:51,690 --> 00:04:52,890
No!

51
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,520
W-Where's Luffy?!

52
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:58,220
"Where," indeed.

53
00:04:58,220 --> 00:05:01,670
He's probably wandering, lost in the forest.

54
00:05:04,980 --> 00:05:06,540
Clima-Tact!

55
00:05:21,660 --> 00:05:23,400
Nami, are you okay?!

56
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:26,110
Yeah! That was close!

57
00:05:26,110 --> 00:05:28,220
Thank you, Usopp!

58
00:05:28,220 --> 00:05:30,420
You cheeky little...

59
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:37,920
Carrot!

60
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,690
Leave it to me!

61
00:05:46,390 --> 00:05:47,860
Eleclaw!

62
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:56,140
It's my turn!

63
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:58,650
Reflection!

64
00:06:04,410 --> 00:06:05,630
Carrot!

65
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,160
Are you okay?!

66
00:06:12,590 --> 00:06:15,980
Carrot's punch came out of the mirror!

67
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:20,550
I'm a mirror!

68
00:06:20,550 --> 00:06:24,020
I ate the Mirror-Mirror Fruit
and became a mirror human!

69
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:34,200
Just like a mirror reflects light,
if you throw a punch at my mirror,

70
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:37,440
it will also reflect it back!

71
00:06:45,130 --> 00:06:46,880
Be careful, Carrot!

72
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:49,540
I'll break your stupid mirror!

73
00:06:49,540 --> 00:06:52,840
Mirro-world!

74
00:06:59,940 --> 00:07:00,960
Carrot!

75
00:07:11,380 --> 00:07:13,380
What did you do to her?!

76
00:07:19,980 --> 00:07:21,830
That's the first!

77
00:07:21,830 --> 00:07:24,940
I can't get out! Let me out!

78
00:07:24,940 --> 00:07:29,150
What did you do?! Let Carrot go!

79
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,150
Stay away, Nami!

80
00:07:29,740 --> 00:07:31,940
I can't do that.

81
00:07:33,260 --> 00:07:34,990
Ah! Nami!

82
00:07:36,460 --> 00:07:37,890
Chopper!

83
00:07:39,060 --> 00:07:40,940
Help me!

84
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:49,080
Mama already knows that you guys are here!

85
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:49,950
What?!

86
00:07:49,950 --> 00:07:54,620
Did you think no one knew?! How idiotic!

87
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:15,930
We're all coming after you now.
Mama ordered us to!

88
00:08:15,930 --> 00:08:17,260
That one...

89
00:08:17,260 --> 00:08:18,630
And them...

90
00:08:18,630 --> 00:08:19,960
Those fools...

91
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:21,460
And him!

92
00:08:21,460 --> 00:08:25,350
We've all been told by Mama that we need to...

93
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:33,020
"let the Straw Hats keep going for now. Just don't let them find Sanji.

94
00:08:33,020 --> 00:08:38,240
Make them regret trying to mess with me!"

95
00:08:45,630 --> 00:08:50,020
Mama knows everything!

96
00:08:56,090 --> 00:08:59,760
Alright, homies! Don't let them escape!

97
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:05,850
You can't get away!

98
00:09:12,060 --> 00:09:13,940
No!

99
00:09:13,940 --> 00:09:15,360
Chopper!

100
00:09:30,090 --> 00:09:32,180
Nami, run!

101
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:36,550
There are too many of them!
If all three of us get caught, we're done for!

102
00:09:37,670 --> 00:09:42,310
They're members of an emperor's crew!
We underestimated them!

103
00:09:42,310 --> 00:09:45,870
Go look for Luffy!
I'll do the best I can here!

104
00:09:46,850 --> 00:09:49,390
Okay! I'll be back!

105
00:09:52,350 --> 00:09:54,140
Rumble!

106
00:09:54,140 --> 00:09:56,050
Monster Point!

107
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:10,870
Look at that! You were already interesting,
but you're able to do this too?!

108
00:10:10,870 --> 00:10:13,910
Mama will be happy!

109
00:10:13,910 --> 00:10:19,900
She doesn't just seek every race; 
she also collects all kinds of strange creatures.

110
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:24,940
Now, catch them!

111
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:31,810
Stop, you brat!

112
00:10:34,340 --> 00:10:35,630
Go away!

113
00:10:38,140 --> 00:10:41,450
Luffy! Where are you?!

114
00:10:45,870 --> 00:10:48,380
Then, I kept running around,

115
00:10:48,380 --> 00:10:51,880
looking for you until it got dark.

116
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:55,560
I see! I'm glad that you found me!

117
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:57,660
All right!

118
00:10:57,660 --> 00:11:01,220
Let's go save Chopper and Carrot right now!
Where are they?!

119
00:11:01,220 --> 00:11:02,500
Right here.

120
00:11:01,890 --> 00:11:02,500
Huh?

121
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:05,800
All of that happened right here.

122
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:11,430
But now, they're all gone.
That's why I'm asking this guy!

123
00:11:11,430 --> 00:11:15,470
You were watching the whole time!
Where's Chopper? And what about Carrot?!

124
00:11:15,470 --> 00:11:20,650
That Brûlée lady and the forest monsters
didn't mess with you at all!

125
00:11:20,650 --> 00:11:22,800
That means you're one of them!

126
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:28,160
Uh... One of them?
Well, we're not enemies...

127
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:33,790
Oh! If you want to know,
bring me some apple juice from over on my left–

128
00:11:33,790 --> 00:11:35,710
We don't have time for that!

129
00:11:35,710 --> 00:11:39,870
If you tell us something useful,
then sure, we'll bring it to you!

130
00:11:39,870 --> 00:11:41,270
Really?!

131
00:11:41,270 --> 00:11:44,040
Yeah, since you've been mentioning it so much, I wanna try it too.

132
00:11:44,680 --> 00:11:46,920
By the way,

133
00:11:46,140 --> 00:11:46,920
Huh?

134
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:49,850
you look pretty strong, but...

135
00:11:52,170 --> 00:11:55,060
are you ?

136
00:11:55,060 --> 00:11:57,860
Y-Yes, I am strong! Why does that matter?

137
00:11:58,580 --> 00:12:02,600
I see. Appearances aren't everything, I guess.

138
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:07,020
That reindeer guy was surprisingly strong,

139
00:12:07,020 --> 00:12:12,370
but the trees of the forest 
attacked him without hesitation.

140
00:12:13,150 --> 00:12:17,660
Once they get an order, they don't stop

141
00:12:17,660 --> 00:12:21,380
until they complete it!

142
00:12:22,890 --> 00:12:27,180
Really? Then, why did they stop attacking me?

143
00:12:29,140 --> 00:12:32,610
When I beat a bunch of them,
they left me alone, too!

144
00:12:32,610 --> 00:12:35,640
Hey, how are they alive, anyways?

145
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:40,220
Every six months,
each resident of Totto Land

146
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:44,070
must pay a month's worth 
of their soul to the kingdom,

147
00:12:44,070 --> 00:12:46,300
in exchange for their safety.

148
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:47,250
Soul?

149
00:12:47,250 --> 00:12:50,400
Yeah, their lifespan, basically.

150
00:12:49,740 --> 00:12:50,400
Huh?!

151
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:54,200
So the people lose two months
of their lifespan in a year...

152
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:58,650
and one year of their lifespan for every six.

153
00:12:58,650 --> 00:12:59,790
How is that possible?

154
00:12:59,790 --> 00:13:05,470
Linlin, I mean, Big Mom
ate the Soul-Soul Fruit.

155
00:13:07,790 --> 00:13:11,420
She can manipulate people's souls.

156
00:13:11,420 --> 00:13:16,510
With that power,
she takes the life span of her citizens.

157
00:13:16,510 --> 00:13:24,490
At that moment, the citizens have to choose 
to stay in Totto Land or leave.

158
00:13:25,210 --> 00:13:29,810
And by spreading the collected souls
all over the country,

159
00:13:29,810 --> 00:13:34,750
all kinds of things take on a life of their own.

160
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:40,710
We call those who came to life "the homies."

161
00:13:41,390 --> 00:13:43,570
The collection and distribution of souls

162
00:13:43,570 --> 00:13:50,680
is handled by Linlin's... um, 
Big Mom's incarnations made of her own soul.

163
00:13:52,430 --> 00:13:55,640
That's what happens in Totto Land.

164
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:59,740
When we first arrived, there were 
lots of odd things alive in the town of chocolate.

165
00:13:59,740 --> 00:14:04,270
Is that why the crocodile was able to talk?! 
And the human-like rabbit?!

166
00:14:04,270 --> 00:14:08,520
Yeah, that's right.
Animals can be personified too.

167
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:11,520
What an incredible ability!

168
00:14:10,190 --> 00:14:11,520
So, what about these guys?

169
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:14,230
They're something else.

170
00:14:14,230 --> 00:14:20,830
Brûlée used her ability to turn normal animals into people.

171
00:14:21,710 --> 00:14:26,680
Oh, by the way, souls can't be 
put into other people or corpses.

172
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:30,840
Why didn't you tell me that before?!
You've been watching me the whole time!

173
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:34,060
Because I didn't want to get involved!

174
00:14:34,060 --> 00:14:37,230
If you didn't want to get involved, then why are you buried here?!

175
00:14:37,230 --> 00:14:39,850
Why?! Who are you?!

176
00:14:41,260 --> 00:14:43,770
Tell me! I'll get you the juice!

177
00:14:43,770 --> 00:14:49,740
O-Okay! I'll tell you! 
Just get off of me! Stop!

178
00:14:54,020 --> 00:15:02,780
Long ago... very long ago, I was Big Mom's...
I mean, the pirate Charlotte Linlin's...

179
00:15:03,940 --> 00:15:05,520
Linlin's...

180
00:15:10,250 --> 00:15:14,240
Linlin's husband!

181
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:15,990
Wh... What?!

182
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:30,520
W-Why is one of the
Three Sweet Commanders here?!

183
00:15:34,230 --> 00:15:38,020
Charlotte Cracker (10th Son)
One of the Three Sweet Commanders of the
Big Mom Pirates and the Minister of Biscuit

184
00:15:36,490 --> 00:15:38,000
Straw Hat!

185
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:43,240
I'm going to...

186
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:45,800
put an end...

187
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:48,090
to your life!

188
00:15:59,870 --> 00:16:01,210
Big Mom's...

189
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:03,470
...ex-husband?!

190
00:16:03,470 --> 00:16:04,760
Uh-huh.

191
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:12,820
She and I had two daughters, and then she threw me out.

192
00:16:15,650 --> 00:16:19,620
It's not that anyone's after me...

193
00:16:19,620 --> 00:16:22,790
They just don't pay attention to me!

194
00:16:29,090 --> 00:16:30,690
W-What?!

195
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:48,520
Who's that?

196
00:17:00,030 --> 00:17:02,640
S-Sir, what brings you here?

197
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:05,870
Am I not allowed to be here?

198
00:17:05,870 --> 00:17:08,880
No! Of course you are.

199
00:17:18,250 --> 00:17:19,600
Hey!

200
00:17:23,810 --> 00:17:26,440
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!

201
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:27,560
What?!

202
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:29,770
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!

203
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:37,070
– His body's coming out!
– Get back, Nami!

204
00:17:37,070 --> 00:17:40,490
No!

205
00:17:48,410 --> 00:17:51,110
We thought he was a giant!

206
00:17:58,790 --> 00:18:05,520
What's wrong with you? What kind of a fool just gives the enemy information like that?!

207
00:18:05,520 --> 00:18:08,590
W-Wait, Cracker-kun !

208
00:18:08,590 --> 00:18:12,900
I want to see my daughter, Chiffon,
even if only for a moment!

209
00:18:14,390 --> 00:18:19,600
I heard she got married!
I want to congratulate her!

210
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:24,350
That's why I need you to let me talk to Linlin!

211
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:28,370
Also, I heard that Lola ran away!

212
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:33,960
They're both my precious daughters!

213
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:35,110
Lola?

214
00:18:36,580 --> 00:18:37,870
Ran away?

215
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:42,200
One of my beloved older sisters

216
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:46,000
ran off to sea to find love.

217
00:18:46,630 --> 00:18:48,380
To seek a match of her own.

218
00:18:48,380 --> 00:18:49,600
Hm?

219
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:52,650
Lola... ran away from home?

220
00:18:52,650 --> 00:18:59,060
Cracker-kun, let go of me!
I just want to see Lola... and Chiffon...

221
00:18:59,060 --> 00:19:02,160
I just want to see my daughters!

222
00:19:03,260 --> 00:19:07,910
Lola... That Lola... Could it be?

223
00:19:08,540 --> 00:19:11,870
Lola, you guys went to the New World?!

224
00:19:11,870 --> 00:19:15,460
We didn't go there! 
We were born in the New World!

225
00:19:15,460 --> 00:19:18,520
Mama is a pirate, too. Ah...

226
00:19:18,520 --> 00:19:19,500
that's right...

227
00:19:20,410 --> 00:19:23,840
This is Mama's vivre card. I'll let you have it.

228
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:25,790
Paper?

229
00:19:25,790 --> 00:19:31,290
Wow! How lucky!
Captain Lola's mama is a great pirate!

230
00:19:31,290 --> 00:19:35,480
Take good care of it!
It'll definitely be useful one day!

231
00:19:38,690 --> 00:19:41,800
Everything's starting to make sense...

232
00:19:40,460 --> 00:19:41,800
Huh?

233
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:46,640
In that case, could... Lola's mama be...

234
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:50,560
Big Mom?!

235
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:56,780
And this man is...

236
00:19:56,780 --> 00:19:59,720
Lola's father?!

237
00:19:59,050 --> 00:19:59,720
What?

238
00:20:22,450 --> 00:20:25,040
They're back!
It's the rabbit and the crane!

239
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:26,410
They're... flying!

240
00:20:31,820 --> 00:20:34,940
Stop! Randolph!

241
00:21:00,130 --> 00:21:02,550
Was that haki?! No, not quite...

242
00:21:02,550 --> 00:21:04,030
What was it then?!

243
00:21:09,820 --> 00:21:10,970
They screamed...

244
00:21:12,870 --> 00:21:14,960
and withered up out of fear?!

245
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:52,740
You must think you're a big shot... 
if you think you're able to get in my way.

246
00:21:53,730 --> 00:21:55,660
Randolph!

247
00:21:57,570 --> 00:21:59,960
I'm sorry. That was his idea.

248
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:02,220
Liar! It was yours!

249
00:22:04,060 --> 00:22:04,800
They can talk!

250
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:07,800
We are very sorry.

251
00:22:09,540 --> 00:22:12,350
Is he someone special?

252
00:22:14,310 --> 00:22:15,810
He looks strong, that's for sure.

253
00:22:17,340 --> 00:22:21,210
Mama always has her next move set in motion.

254
00:22:21,210 --> 00:22:25,240
Since Straw Hat Luffy defeated Doflamingo,

255
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:29,650
she knew Brûlée would have trouble,
so she sent me.

256
00:22:29,650 --> 00:22:33,310
I can't just let you say that, Big Brother!

257
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:49,590
Whoa! A tree monster!

258
00:22:52,140 --> 00:22:53,740
Oh, that woman!

259
00:22:53,740 --> 00:22:55,970
If she ordered me to do it,

260
00:22:55,970 --> 00:22:57,340
I would have killed them at once!

261
00:22:56,300 --> 00:22:59,080
Kingbaum
Master of the Seducing Woods

262
00:22:57,340 --> 00:22:59,080
That's right!

263
00:22:59,080 --> 00:23:01,560
We members of the Seducing Woods team

264
00:23:01,560 --> 00:23:06,170
have never allowed a single target 
of ours to leave alive!

265
00:23:06,170 --> 00:23:09,360
Oh! It's not just Minister Cracker 
and Madame Brûlée...

266
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:11,030
Master Kingbaum is here, too!

267
00:23:11,030 --> 00:23:14,240
I can't believe all three of them are here at the same time!

268
00:23:15,210 --> 00:23:18,710
That's nice and all, but we can't waste any time.

269
00:23:20,780 --> 00:23:22,870
By the midday tomorrow,

270
00:23:22,870 --> 00:23:27,940
the Vinsmoke siblings will arrive 
at Whole Cake Chateau.

271
00:23:28,910 --> 00:23:35,600
Forming a family connection with the Vinsmokes 
is something that Mama has wanted for a long time.

272
00:23:42,190 --> 00:23:47,130
We'll have Germa 66's formidable military
and advanced technology.

273
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:50,360
I know that!

274
00:24:02,680 --> 00:24:04,460
They've turned into animals!

275
00:24:07,390 --> 00:24:10,690
And... why is that branch talking?!

276
00:24:10,690 --> 00:24:11,900
I'm not a branch!

277
00:24:11,900 --> 00:24:14,300
Look at this, Straw Hat!

278
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:17,230
Oh, Luffy!

279
00:24:17,230 --> 00:24:19,980
Luffy, Nami! Help!

280
00:24:19,980 --> 00:24:20,930
What?!

281
00:24:21,430 --> 00:24:22,560
Chopper got caught, too?!

282
00:24:23,260 --> 00:24:26,440
What happened to you guys?!
What are you doing in there?!

283
00:24:26,440 --> 00:24:32,030
She trapped us in the mirror!
She has a mirror ability! Be careful!

284
00:24:35,140 --> 00:24:38,100
How's this, Brother Cracker?!

285
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:41,230
I've already got these fools...

286
00:24:41,910 --> 00:24:44,060
by the scruffs of their necks!

287
00:24:57,340 --> 00:25:01,390
Hey, Chopper! Carrot! Are you okay?!

288
00:25:02,570 --> 00:25:03,920
We're fine!

289
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:06,360
We're not hurt at all!

290
00:25:07,100 --> 00:25:13,020
It's just the mirror that broke.
We're safe in this dimension!

291
00:25:13,020 --> 00:25:14,570
So you're okay!

292
00:25:14,570 --> 00:25:17,060
I don't know what you're talking about, 
but that's good.

293
00:25:17,060 --> 00:25:19,170
Luffy! Listen...

294
00:25:20,780 --> 00:25:25,080
Whatever.
Let's start with this blabbermouth.

295
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:29,700
W-What are you gonna do to me?!

296
00:25:29,700 --> 00:25:31,700
Mama said I can kill you.

297
00:25:31,700 --> 00:25:33,990
What?!

298
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:40,500
Th-Think about it!

299
00:25:40,500 --> 00:25:45,600
I'm your stepfather, Cracker-kun !

300
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:49,240
You used to be! Not anymore!

301
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:54,360
Mama considers her 
43 ex-husbands as strangers,

302
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:56,800
unrelated to us by blood.

303
00:25:57,560 --> 00:25:59,160
How dare you!

304
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:04,080
But I'm definitely related to my daughters by blood!

305
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:04,080
Enough!

306
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:09,950
I just want to congratulate my daughter!

307
00:26:44,250 --> 00:26:45,500
Is this sympathy?

308
00:26:46,700 --> 00:26:50,750
After seeing someone dozens of times, 
they tend to grow on you!

309
00:26:57,150 --> 00:26:58,840
Th-Thank you!

310
00:26:58,840 --> 00:27:00,590
Thank you!

311
00:27:17,510 --> 00:27:19,820
This isn't good!

312
00:27:19,820 --> 00:27:23,890
Minister Cracker is gonna start a fight here!

313
00:27:23,890 --> 00:27:29,390
Homies!
Catch those two so we can finish this!

314
00:27:29,390 --> 00:27:31,240
It's not safe here! Let's run!

315
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:34,380
Hurry up!

316
00:27:36,950 --> 00:27:38,820
We'll take care of them!

317
00:27:38,820 --> 00:27:40,920
Don't let them get away!

318
00:27:45,460 --> 00:27:47,520
Hey, what's your name?!

319
00:27:47,520 --> 00:27:49,500
I'm Pound.

320
00:27:52,430 --> 00:27:56,620
Did you mention Lola before?

321
00:27:56,070 --> 00:27:56,620
Yeah.

322
00:27:56,620 --> 00:27:58,940
Hang on a second...

323
00:27:59,900 --> 00:28:01,380
Um...

324
00:28:06,080 --> 00:28:06,810
Found it!

325
00:28:15,570 --> 00:28:17,450
What's that?

326
00:28:17,450 --> 00:28:21,780
It's the vivre card of my friend Lola's mom.

327
00:28:21,780 --> 00:28:24,800
But I don't know if it's Big Mom's or not...

328
00:28:28,100 --> 00:28:31,870
What are you doing?!
What's wrong, guys?!

329
00:28:33,450 --> 00:28:36,000
What's wrong, Kingbaum?!
Even you're stopping?!

330
00:28:36,980 --> 00:28:40,110
We can't do it, Brûlée!

331
00:28:39,400 --> 00:28:40,110
What?

332
00:28:40,110 --> 00:28:43,950
We homies cannot fight against her!

333
00:28:43,950 --> 00:28:45,340
Wha...? Why not?!

334
00:28:45,340 --> 00:28:48,810
I can sense Mama's powerful soul!

335
00:28:48,810 --> 00:28:50,080
Huh?!

336
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:50,930
What?

337
00:29:01,620 --> 00:29:06,970
No way...! Is this really... 
Big Mom's vivre card?!

338
00:29:17,860 --> 00:29:20,000
Luffy! No way.

339
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:20,000
Are you okay?

340
00:29:28,860 --> 00:29:31,600
C-Cracker-kun !

341
00:29:34,580 --> 00:29:36,020
He has more than two arms!

342
00:29:36,020 --> 00:29:37,760
Damn!

343
00:29:38,840 --> 00:29:40,420
That bastard!

344
00:29:40,420 --> 00:29:47,800
I'm Biscuit Knight Cracker,
one of the Three Sweet Commanders.

345
00:29:47,800 --> 00:29:50,390
Also known as...

346
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:54,020
"Thousand Arms" Cracker.

347
00:29:54,020 --> 00:29:57,960
If I tap my arm once, it turns into two.

348
00:29:57,960 --> 00:30:01,020
If I do it again...

349
00:30:02,860 --> 00:30:04,640
it turns into three.

350
00:30:04,640 --> 00:30:05,650
What?!

351
00:30:05,650 --> 00:30:07,380
They'll keep multiplying.

352
00:30:14,290 --> 00:30:16,770
His legs have multiplied, too.

353
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:21,500
Don't even dream about defeating me.

354
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:24,780
"Thousand Arms" Cracker
One of the Three Sweet Commanders of the
Big Mom Pirates
Bounty: 860 Million Belly

355
00:30:21,500 --> 00:30:24,760
I won't let you interfere with Mama's tea party!

356
00:30:24,760 --> 00:30:26,680
You've got extra limbs. So what?!

357
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:28,490
Gear Second!

358
00:30:31,630 --> 00:30:33,990
Gum-Gum...

359
00:30:34,750 --> 00:30:35,790
Jet...

360
00:30:36,170 --> 00:30:38,120
Bullet!

361
00:30:39,890 --> 00:30:42,000
Gum-Gum...

362
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:43,800
Hawk Whip!

363
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:57,740
Luffy! No! Don't make this a serious fight!
That isn't our goal here!

364
00:30:57,740 --> 00:31:00,520
We need to get out of here to get Sanji-kun back!

365
00:31:03,400 --> 00:31:05,820
I make every fight serious...

366
00:31:05,820 --> 00:31:08,760
I don't know any other way!
